cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Protocol Performance Evaluation Across Seven Implementations
abstract: The dataset documents a systematic measurement campaign comparing seven
  distinct QUIC protocol libraries under controlled network conditions. For each library,
  client‑server transfers of varying file sizes were executed with optional bandwidth
  limits while recording transfer duration, energy consumption, and integrity checksums.
  An evaluation script aggregated per‑run logs to compute goodput, statistical summaries,
  and success rates, producing JSON reports, visualizations, and tabular data for
  further analysis. The collection provides reproducible performance metrics and methodological
  details for QUIC implementation benchmarking.
